www.softwareqa.us 

Introduction
This code is written in Java and very handy for to run selenium code in specific browsers.

Initial steps
Go to this URL: https://www.seleniumhq.org/download/
Scroll down and you will find all the listed browsers.
Click on any you want to use. To download click on “latest” anchor tag.
 
Download the required file as per your operating system and save on local machine. 

 
Browsers Code
Syntax:
System.setProperty(“webdriver.name.driver”,”File path to .exe file ”);
WebDriver driver = new drivername();


CHROME:
System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver","C:\\yourpath\\comes\\here\\chromedriver.exe");
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();


FIREFOX:
System.setProperty("webdriver.gecko.driver","C:\\yourpath\\comes\\here\\geckodriver.exe");		
WebDriver driver = new FirefoxDriver();

IE:
System.setProperty("webdriver.ie.driver","C:\\yourpath\\comes\\here\\IEDriverServer.exe");
WebDriver driver = new InternetExplorerDriver();
